snippet.description:

Bang! / My Brother, My Brother and Me / The Worst Idea of All Time / Bad With Money / Pod Save America / Underunderstood / The Allusionist / The Dollop / You’re Wrong About / The Purrrcast / LORE / Hello from the Magic Tavern / Whatever Happened to Pizza at McDonald’s? / Song Exploder / Maintenance Phase / Hidden Brain / Planet Money / 99% Invisible

The voice of Michelle Nguyen is Kate Jones.

snippet.title: The First Ten Years, Year 5: 2014
snippet.description:
A sometimes hilarious, occasionally heartbreaking, and always entertaining joint memoir by Joseph Fink, cocreator of Welcome to Night Vale, and his wife, writer and performer Meg Bashwiner, chronicling the first ten years of their relationship from both sides.

There are two sides to every love story.

Coming May 11th.

Pre-order your copy at your local bookstore  or go to welcometonightvale.com/books for personalized, signed editions.

THE FIRST TEN YEARS BOOK TOUR!

Joseph and Meg will be on a virtual book tour in May. Come see them live online via these fantastic booksellers:

MAY 11 - Politics & Prose (DC), in conversation with Dylan Marron

MAY 12 - Oblong Books (NY), in conversation with Jeffrey Cranor

MAY 13 - Powell’s (OR), in conversation with Symphony Sanders

MAY 14 - Brookline Booksmith (MA), in conversation with Erin McKeown

MAY 17 - Malaprop’s Bookstore (NC), in conversation with Jonny Sun

MAY 19 - The Booksmith (CA), in conversation with Mara Wilson

MAY 20 - Books & Books (FL)

MAY 24 - Anderson’s Bookshop (IL), in conversation with Hal Lublin

snippet.title: The First Ten Years, Year 1: 2009
snippet.description:
A sometimes hilarious, occasionally heartbreaking, and always entertaining joint memoir by Joseph Fink, cocreator of Welcome to Night Vale, and his wife, writer and performer Meg Bashwiner, chronicling the first ten years of their relationship from both sides.

There are two sides to every love story.

Coming May 11th.

Pre-order your copy at your local bookstore  or go to welcometonightvale.com/books for personalized, signed editions.

snippet.title: Faceless Old Woman Book Release-a-thon! March 24, 3-7pm ET
snippet.description:
Authors Joseph Fink & Jeffrey Cranor (along with many special guests) celebrate the release of their new Night Vale novel: THE FACELESS OLD WOMAN WHO SECRETLY LIVES IN YOUR HOME. Available now wherever you buy books!

Join for any or all of this 4-hour book extravaganza, beginning at 3pm ET / 12pm PT on Tuesday, March 24. We'll talk about the book, perform a reading, and answer audience questions. And we'll have some really amazing guests join us along the way. 

BUY THE BOOK / SUPPORT LOCAL BOOKSTORES!
* BOOKS ARE MAGIC (Brooklyn) https://booksaremagic.net/facelessoldwoman
* SIGNED COPIES! OBLONG BOOKS (Hudson Valley NY) https://www.oblongbooks.com/book/9780062889003
* NORTHSHIRE (Saratoga Springs NY) https://www.northshire.com/book/9780062889003  
* BOULDER BOOK STORE (Colorado) https://www.boulderbookstore.net/book/9780062889003
* ANDERSON’S BOOKSHOP (Chicago) https://www.andersonsbookshop.com/book/9780062889003
* POWELL’S BOOKS https://www.powells.com/book/-9780062889003
* BOOKSMITH (San Francisco) https://www.booksmith.com/book/9780062889003
* KEPLER’S BOOKS (Menlo Park CA) https://www.keplers.com/book/9780062889003

snippet.title: News about books and tours, and "Our Plague Year"
snippet.description:
TUESDAY MARCH 24, 3-7PM EASTERN: Join us here for a 4 hour marathon live stream to celebrate the release of our new book The Faceless Old Woman Who Secretly Lives In Your Home. With special guests including Justin and Travis McElroy, Dessa, Mara Wilson, Jonny Son, and bunch of other surprise guests.

Joseph has a few things to chat about with you, and then we present the first episode of our new show, Our Plague Year.

Introducing a new kind of current events podcast. An island in a storm of bad headlines. An experiment in public anxiety. Let's get through this year together.

Subscribe at http://ourplagueyear.libsyn.com/ or wherever you get your podcasts.

Written and produced by Joseph Fink

"Don't Look for the Helpers" by Cory Doctorow

"Social Distances" by Nisi Shawl 

The song "This Too Shall Pass" by Danny Schmidt 

All other music by Joseph Fink

Logo artwork by Jessica Hayworth

A production of Night Vale Presents

snippet.title: Start With This: Idea to Execution
snippet.description:
A brand new podcast from Night Vale Presents, and the first podcast Joseph Fink and Jeffrey Cranor have made together since Welcome to Night Vale: Start With This, a podcast gone creativity playground designed to put your ideas in motion. Each episode centers around a topic from world building, to opening lines, and even failure. Then they give listeners two short assignments: something to consume and something to create. The best way to start writing is to start writing. Not sure where to begin? Start With This.

To keep listening to Start With This, subscribe on Apple Podcasts, Spotify, or your favorite podcast app.

//

There’s natural talent, and then there’s practice. You can only control that last bit. Joseph and Jeffrey talk building habits of creation so that starting projects gets into your muscle memory.

Consume:

Check out Jonathan Mann’s Song A Day Youtube channel. Jonathan’s been writing and recording a song a day for over 3,000 days— it’s the ultimate example of flexing the habit of creation: https://www.youtube.com/user/therockcookiebottom

Create:

Pick an idea that you’ve had for a while. Take exactly 1 hour to work on it exclusively. This can be one continuous hour, or 30 minutes for two days, or 10 minutes for six days. Then put it out there (written or recorded) on our Membership Community, your website, or shout it to a bird from your porch. Consider this your first try of many at this idea.

Join the SWT Membership community to see what other listeners are making: https://www.patreon.com/startwiththis

Credits: Jeffrey Cranor (host) & Joseph Fink (host), Julia Melfi (producer), Grant Stewart (editor), Vincent Cacchione (mixer). Rob Wilson (logo). Produced by Night Vale Presents.

http://www.startwiththispodcast.com
http://www.nightvalepresents.com

snippet.title: I Only Listen to the Mountain Goats: Episode 1, The Best Ever Death Metal Band in Denton
snippet.description:
John Darnielle and Joseph Fink discuss the role in their lives of art, faith, and satan with John Green, author of The Fault in Our Stars and the upcoming Turtles All The Way Down. And we learn why making the job of creating art more difficult can sometimes make the art itself better. Premiering a new cover by Laura Jane Grace of Against Me!

 Buy Laura Jane Grace’s cover of “The Best Ever Death Metal Band in Denton” on  iTunes, Bandcamp, or wherever you buy digital music. It supports both the artist and the show!

 Pre-order the full cover album on vinyl and digital: http://smarturl.it/I-Only-Listen

 Learn more about John Darnielle’s two novels here: http://www.johndarnielle.comListen to more music by the Mountain Goats, including their latest album Goths, here: http://www.mountain-goats.com

snippet.title: Conversations with People Who Hate Me: Episode 1, You're a Piece of Sh*t
snippet.description:
A new weekly podcast from Night Vale Presents.

 Dylan Marron makes popular social justice videos on the internet, so he gets a lot of hate messages. In the first episode of this podcast, he speaks with Chris, a man who called Dylan “a piece of sh*t”... among many other things.

 Subscribe now wherever you listen to podcasts.

 Conversations with People Who Hate Me is a production of Night Vale Presents. Credits: Dylan Marron (creator, producer, host), Christy Gressman (executive producer), Vincent Cacchione (audio engineer, mixer), Alen Rahimic (production manager). Theme song: “These Dark Times” by Caged Animals.  More info: www.nightvalepresents.com

snippet.title: The Orbiting Human Circus of the Air: Season One, Episode 1
snippet.description:
Welcome to the world of The Orbiting Human Circus: discover the surreally impossible radio show broadcast from the top of the Eiffel Tower, meet the lonely janitor who longs to become part of it, and settle in for the chilling tale of Goolsby and Rue.

NOTE:To continue listening to The Orbiting Human Circus (of the Air), subscribe now via iTunes (https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/orbiting-human-circus-air/id1158759190) or via RSS on your favorite podcatcher (http://orbitinghumancircus.libsyn.com/rss)

Thanks to Rocket Mortgage by Quicken Loans and Atom Tickets for supporting the show! Download the free Atom Tickets app from Google Play or the Apple App Store and use code OHC for $5 off through the end of the year. Check out Rocket Mortgage at http://QuickenLoans.com/OHC.

Featuring John Cameron Mitchell as Mr. Cameron, Julian Koster as the Janitor, and Drew Callander as the Narrator. For full credits, go to http://www.orbitinghumancircus.com.

Written and created by Julian Koster. Co-directed by and developed with Ellie Heyman. Produced by Christy Gressman. Featuring musical composition and arrangement by Thomas Hughes and music by The Music Tapes.

In November 2016, the Janitor will be cleaning a venue near you! See tour dates at http://www.orbitinghumancircus.com.

Part of the Night Vale Presents network. http://nightvalepresents.com

snippet.title: Making of the Welcome to Night Vale Audiobook
snippet.description:
Cecil Baldwin and Dylan Marron give us a peek behind the scenes at the recording of the audiobook for Welcome to Night Vale: A Novel. 

Release date: October 20, 2015. 

Pre-order the audiobook at http://amazon.com and at http://www.harpercollins.com/9780062351463/welcome-to-night-vale-cd

Pre-order the novel at most places where books are sold.

Book tour! Authors Joseph Fink & Jeffrey Cranor will be touring US and Canadian cities from October 21 - November 22, along with some very special guest moderators. Visit http://welcometonightvale.com and click on Live Shows for a complete book tour schedule (as well as Night Vale live shows coming to a town near you).

snippet.title: A Big Announcement from Night Vale
snippet.description:
Hey friends,

We have a YouTube Channel. We also have a big announcement about a US Tour. We also have a new episode today. And an archive of old episodes.

So subscribe to this channel for new Night Vale podcast episodes on the 1st and 15th of each month.

Also, visit http://welcometonightvale.com for information on live shows, FAQs, donor benefits, and more!

Here's every city on our 2015 US Tour (March 26 - May 20):
Philadelphia, DC, Chapel Hill, Charleston, Jacksonville, Fort Lauderdale, Clearwater, Atlanta, Nashville, Birmingham, Memphis, New Orleans, Houston, San Antonio, Dallas, Tucson, Mesa, Las Vegas, Los Angeles, San Pedro, Oakland, Portland, Seattle, Spokane, Missoula, Fargo, Minneapolis, Iowa City, Lawrence, St Louis, Chicago, Bloomington, Detroit, Louisville, Cincinnati, Cleveland, Pittsburgh, Buffalo, Albany, Northampton, Boston
